3.2.0.0 - (Saruu's Coffee)
- [New] Moved The Debug Tools Into The Settings Tab - [Changed] The Debug Tools Link In The About Tab To "Make It Rain" Now Pops Up A Lil' Message - [Fixed] Just Fixed Sum' Tooltips (Too Gansta For Literature) - [New, Does This Count] Spaced The Changelog Texts - [New] Splashscreen Totally Redesigned - [New] New Logo By Saruu a.k.a. My Bro (Vaughan R. K.) - [New] The Ceslyn Random Message Fixer - [New] UDP Flooder Timer Interval's Value Now Gets Saved In My.Settings - [New] Restore Settings - [New] Saves When You Choose Normal Havok Skin or Visual Styles Skin - [Fixed] Whenb About Form Is Showing Already and You Go To The Notify Icon and Click About Havok You Get An Error - [Changed] I Think I Changed The "StartupDepotChecker" and Moved It To The Splashscreen - [Changed] The Caption Font For The "License Agreement" and "What's New!" Window To Like 10 Font Size Ubuntu Font - [Changed] The Settings UI, I Think - [Changed] The XUL Installer No Longer Uses That BackgroundWorker - [Changed] The UI of XUL Installer - [Changed] Balloon Tips Pop Up When Installing and Finished Installing A XUL Application. - [New] Lockdown Mode's Active or Deactive Status Now Gets Saved In My.Settings - [New] Added Homepage Functionality To The Web Browser - [New] Set The Homepage URL - [New] Fixed Up The Settings Tab - [New] Added Net Monitor - [New] Added Text In Status Bar For Network Connected, True or False - [New] Added StatusBar - [New] Added Progress Bar - [Removed] Useless Feed Text and Its Webbrowser - [Notice] Encryption-Level Weapon/Tool Is Still Broken - [New] Cookies Manager for The Web browser. This allows clearing of all cookis and importing a cookie.
-----------------------------------------------
3.1.0.0 - (Machine)
- New View-Source, Has Syntax Highlighting (Please Correct My Terminololgy If Incorrect) - All Internet Explorere Wrappers Have Been Deleted and Replaced With GeckoFX, This Brings Way More Functionality and Is Faster, Navigations Run On A Seperate Thread - Just Fixed Some Tiny UI Issues - Added License Tab For Gecko - Removed That Shitty Depot Installer Tab, Havok Will Now Start A Seperate Thread On Startup To See If Depot Files Are There - The Updater Has Been Made Way More Awesome, Next Release Will Make It Even Better - Added Timer Interval For The UDP Flooder (Timer) Under The Settings Tab In The About Window - Added Settings Tab Under About Window - The Groupbox Called "Weapons" Has Been Renamed/Titled With "Weapons/Tools" - When You haven't Selected A valid Tool The Msgbox Display "Please Select A Weapon/Tool" Different From What It usually Said, "Please Select Your Weapon!"
-----------------------------------------------
3.0.0.0 - (Planet Orbital Spheron Trinx)
Welcome To P-O-S-T! The Newest Best and Best Release of Havok Ever! Packed With Amazing Features. Beautiful GUI, But Not Just The Interface Also The Code!
- Added The Weapons Selection - New About Dialog - Improved The Working of The "Visit The Deavmi HUB" Link. It Will Now Open Up In Your Deafult Web Browser - Added DotNetToolbar TextBox Which Allows You To Get The IP of A URL When Hitting Enter (Or Something Like That) While In Text Mode With No IP Address Dots - Disabled Context Menus On All Browsers - Added Our Custom Context Menu To The Web Browser On The Main Form a.k.a Havok Flood Page - Added Underscores To Buttons, Allowing Button Clicks Using Letters On Keyboards Once The Alt Key Has Been Pressed Down - Added The Experimental Tab In The About Window - Added DotNetToolbar Tooltips To The Buttons - Added The Depot Install Wizard - Added The Remote-PC Weapon - The Log Responds To The Webbrowsers Navigating and Navigated Event Arguments - Added A License Agreement On First Startup - Added Inspiration Quotation From DEavmi When You Click The Q Button - Added The HGetter Weapon - The Updates Window Now Does The Download On A Seperate Thread Making The Application Run Smoother and Betta' - Added The Chesta GUI Under The Experimental Tab (We Will Move This To A Settings Area/Tab/Window Later) - Added Avaliable Physical Memory - Added Avaliable Virtuel Memory - Added The News Tab Will Features A News Page - Eliris Did Not Own The UDP Flooder Code, Soz, It Was By Some Random Called 0nix, Fixed The Credits - The Exit Window Opens Up Now As A Dialog - The Exit Window Has Had Its Icon Removed - The Exit Window Doesn't Appear In The Taskbar - The Ext Window Has No Minimize Box - The Exit Window Has No Minimize Box - Added A Notify Icon To Havok - New Splashscreen - Added A Digital Clock - Added The DotNetToolbar Textboxes, The Textboxes Are Now Watermarked - The Check For Updates Window Has Had Its Minimize Box Removed - The Check For Updates Window Has No Icon Now - The Check For Updates Window Will Not Appear In The Taskbar - The Log Now Displays The Version of Havok - The Log Now Displays The Copyright of Havok - Added A Button To Enable/Disable Windows Visual Styles Skin - Web Browser Has Its Own Address Bar - Web Browser Has Status Text - Web Browser Has Progress Bar - Added A Debug Tools Tool (I Troll You With A Trollie Ne. Soz.) - There Is Now A Text That Updates All Feeds and It's Self Is A Feed Text. - You Can Now Clear The Log text/Items Be Selecting Clear Log On The Log When Right Clicking For A Context Menu - And Mabye There Are More Features, I Think (ADHD Ya Know)
By The Way This Release Is Dedicated To My Best Friends
